	   <a name=97314564318640></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f97314564318640><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=9&mid=97314564318640>Winadann</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=9&mid=97314564318640#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Nov 2nd 1:14 AM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hello, I need some advice and help with my lvl 10 Barbarian Shaman.&nbsp;&nbsp;What equipment should i have, right now i am in Full Banded, armed with a Blacked Mace, and a FS spear.  A few items that increase Wis and that is all what do I need.  Weapon wise. (i prefer the spear for a wp its a style thing) Armour, is the Barbarian armour any good (the racial stuff) and where should i hunt, i have almost no money down to about 10 plat now and need an idea of where to hunt and where to and how to make some coin.   any help would be welcomed.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
	   </form></table><ul>
<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%>
	   <a name=97320952720537></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f97320952720537><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=9&mid=97320952720537>RE: Winadann</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=9&mid=97320952720537#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=492><span id=Sage>Gorthin</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>149 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Nov 2nd 6:58 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.68]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>At level 10 you have several options.&nbsp;&nbsp;In fact, tons.  Full banded is great for level 10, so you are set there.  If you are set on going for something, +mana for the short run, or +wis for the long.  + mana would do you more good at this level, but +wis is what you will end up wanting later.  But I digress =)<br>As to making money, here are a couple suggestions:<br><br>a) Steamfont, by the mino caves, hunting the 5 skeletons spawn.  You will end up with so many bone chips by the time you hit 12 or 13 and decide to move on, it will be sick.  just sell these to players, who will oftentimes pay 2 plat or more per stack of 20.<br><br>b)If you have a magic weapon, The Island in Erud's crossing, aka Wisp Island.  Lightstones and greater lightstones, what more needs to be said?  Also East or West Commons has a healthy supply of wisps.<br><br>c)Bandits in the Karanas.  Sashes, occasional bronze weapons.  Will need a group to do this, as the casters are &gt;evil&lt; at that level.<br><br>d) Blackburrow.  Lots of trains, but a steady supply of cloth and rusty weapons.  Yeah, it is not sexy, but with a high base str, and a few backpacks, you can make several plat per trip.<br><br>e) Crushbone.  Lego pads and belts sell well to players, along with rusty and cloth.<br><br>f) N Ro.  Dervishes.  Occasional Bronze weapons.<br><br>Those are some of the popular spots.  I would just make sure you end up with a decent weapon for each type (until you are deadset on what kind you want, as it may bite you in later levels), magic if you want to hunt wisps, and go at it.  Getting donations for SoW will also help the money flow, but if you do not constantly watch the money, it will add up.<br><br>Gorthin Spiritcaller<br>46 Shaman Bristlebane<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
