	   <tr><td colspan=2>Raise your Charisma. I have tested my resist rates with my shaman using my paw of opalla and no CHA buff vs using a crude stein and CHA buff. I have found that I am resisted FAR less with the high charisma when casting any debuff (Turgor, Malise, Listless, ECT.) I have not seen any difference on casting our dots but our debuffs are the spells resisted the most anyway. It would make sense that CHA is helpful as it is listed as a main stat of shaman upon creation. Try it out and see for yourself.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
