	   <a name=97261110130808></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f97261110130808><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=9&mid=97261110130808>RE: shaman help</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=9&mid=97261110130808#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=492><span id=Sage>Gorthin</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>149 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Oct 26th 9:45 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.68]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>In reality, anytime is a good time to group, although I generally waited until after level 10.&nbsp;&nbsp;Those first ten levels give you the feel of what your character is like.  Not the whole picture, mind you, but a foundation.  <br>     Realistically, group ASAP if that is your long term goal.  Not so much to "go after the big game", but to build that friend list.  Once you get higer level, having a extensive selection of friends is important if you are a group oriented person.  Trying to do pick up groups throughout your EQ experience &gt;can&lt; work, but usually doesn't.  Especially later on (45+) when people are reluctant to trust their character's life (aka playing time and phat l3wt) to someone they do not know.<br>     I am sure someone will try to tell you that soloing is faster xp.  It is, to some extent.  Early on, solo is the way to go.  But later, a small, efficient group (four people or less) can literally rake in the xp.  I went from 37 to 45 in Overthere in a matter of a week and a day or two.  Level 40 took me two days, but each other level we accomplished in a single day.  I could not have done this without a group of friends =)<br><br>Gorthin<br>45 Barbarian Shaman Bristlebane<br>Semi MIA with the release of PS2<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
