	   <tr><td colspan=2>If you make a trip to Lake Rathe in the near future, fellow shammies, I would ask you to investigate an area of Lake Rathe about which little is known and seemingly even less is written.<br><br>As proud owners of the spell "Enduring Breath" we have the abilities to explore areas that are difficult if not impossible for most of the other classes to reach-- underwater locations!<br><br>I, quite by accident, came upon a tunnel in the ground underwater on the backside of the island in Lake Rathe commonly known as "Flame Island", "The Diving Board", or "3 Spawn Island" while attempting to follow ol' Webclaw.&nbsp;&nbsp;If you slip through the gap in the hill to the other side of "Flame" and go into the water, right beneath you is a tunnel which leads off for quite a ways.  Interestingly, it has two branches, one of which leads to an underwater castle.  The other heads off to another island.<br><br>I got no further than looking at the outside of the castle because guarding it were Deepwater Goblins who conned red to me at L30.  There were doors leading inside or perhaps to another zone along the base of the building.<br><br>My question is this:  Has anybody any experience with this spot?   And can they confirm the rumor that there is a dragon who lives inside?<br><br>There is no info on the other portion of this guide refering to zone strategies about this place.  Maybe some of you high level chars can shed light on this mystery!  By the way, Webclaw did not go inside, he continued on around the zone and judging by the /shouts going on, he proceeded to slaughter people by the dozens.  He does drop the Water Crystal staff every time. <br><br>Good luck, young (troll) shammies!<br>&nbsp;<br>Emperor and Shamanic High Priest of the Trolls<br>"Worship Innoruuk, you worthless cattle!"<br></td></tr>
