	   <tr><td colspan=2>&nbsp;&nbsp;   Well, it's not a problem if there is a friend who can hold your stuff for you while you begin a new character, but if you feel you have invested enough time in this one that you don't wish to start over, there are really no bad initial stat choices that will truly disable you over the long haul.  The makers of this game have designed it so you can put numbers in any particular stat and not be overly handicapped if you believe you made a wrong choice.  That said, there are certain stats in which it would benefit you early in the game to have points allocated to "primary" stats (WIS comes to mind..), at least until you earn enough money to buy items which enhance those areas you are lacking in.<br>     The numbers you have posted are by no means fatal, rather, it will result in lower prices for things you buy, higher prices for things you sell, the ability to melee longer without getting tired, and you STILL have more Wisdom than your opening stats.  All-in-all, not a "bad" choice!<br>     Good luck, young shammy!<br><br>&nbsp;<br>Emperor and Shamanic High Priest of the Trolls<br>"Worship Innoruuk, you worthless cattle!"<br></td></tr>
