	   <tr><td colspan=2>As a shaman you should be able to keep two diffrent weapon skills near lvl.&nbsp;&nbsp;Here are my recomadations for weapons by lvl.  This assumes you will be getting the weapons yourself.  <br><br>lvl 1-10 Cracked Staff.  this 1hb will out damage any other newbie weapon in the game.  <br><br>lvl 10-20 Bloodforged Hammer This again is one of the better damage weapon and the +10 MR will help you reduce rooting.  Much better than the runed totem staff.  If you switch at lvl 10 spend 20 training points on 2hb to get your skill up.  <br><br>From here on I suggest using 2hb as your main weapon and also spend time using a spear to get your skill up in piercing.  Of course a JCP and CGS is the goal of many shaman.  The Diffrence between the total wisdom of this combo and The Mortiticators Staff is very small and if you don't plan to move on to the uber weapon and can obtain a MS there is no need to gain skill in piercing.  Also there are some high wisdom 1hb that are as good as the JCP.  In short the only weapon that give a lot more wisdom is the uber weapon.  other than that any class of weapon has a weapon that is as good as any other class.  The bigest diffrence is of all the high wis weapon the JCP is the easyest one to get.  <br><br>Other good 2hb's <br>Glowing Wooden Crook<br>Staff of the Observer<br>Moriticators Staff (very rare)<br><br>Good spears are hard to come by at lower lvl and the most popular JCP can be obtained solo at lvl 44.  <br><br>The weapon is most important before pet lvls.  After lvl 34 your dots and pets will do most of the damage.  After lvl 39 wisdom should be the major factor in choising a weapon. <br><br><br><br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
